-- CZECH DAYBOOK: Czech Policy Makers Speak at Conference in Prague
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2012-06-27T03:22:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/czech-daybook-czech-policy-makers-speak-at-conference-in-prague.html
Top policy makers are scheduled to
speak about economic developments and government policies at the
UniCredit Bank conference in Prague.  All Times in CET (ET+6)  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Prime Minister Petr Necas, Finance Minister Miroslav Kalousek
and Central bank Governor Miroslav Singer are scheduled to speak
at UniCredit Bank conference held in Prague. (12.00 p.m.)  EQUITIES:
* CEZ AS (CEZ CP) may rise for a third day after the biggest
Czech utility said it agreed to sell one coal-fired power plant
to avoid an anti-monopoly fine and as the price of electricity
increased. CEZ advanced 1 percent to 739.5 koruna.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague at 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
